What a GLORIOUS night presenting at @warnerbrothers for The Voice Arts Awards ✨💗🎤🍸Thank you to the incomparable @joanthevoice @rudygaskins1  for creating @societyvoicearts  to celebrate, cultivate and illuminate the beautiful world 🌎 of Voice Acting. 
You have brought talent, producers, casting, and so many other folks from around the GLOBE to celebrate the achievements from everything, EVERY corner of VO. 
Commercials, promo, announcers, audiobook talent, Podcasters, demo, producers, visionaries, iconic voice, actors, and so much more. 
The passion and dedication to @societyvoicearts  and your incredible @thatsvoiceover helps all of us who are fortunate enough to be in this business. 
I’ve had the privilege to meet and work with talented and intriguing people from around the world. 
I continue to be inspired, grateful and proud to be amongst vibrant new friends and long time colleagues. 
So proud of all the nominees and winners!  CONGRATULATIONS TO ALL!! 🎉🤩🎤🍸💋🕎
NEVER stop following your dreams. Stay in community and as my beautiful, talented and graceful friend @jhalegram said, when she was awarded Icon of the Year, you are enough!!! Celebrate all the wins between the bookings. 
And ALWAYS stay in the “weeeeeeeee!!”, the PLAYING, the abandonment, the joy, the utter joy of creating characters.
My mentor, my forever friend, my soulmate, and my personal spirit human @the_charlieadler said these invaluable words while excepting his much deserved #OutstandingBodyOfWork award 🥇 
May you all continue to find your joy, your gratitude and childlike, “weeeee!!” in your work!!
This business can be isolating. As much as we love being in our pajamas and working from home, find your tribe, join a workout group, and create new paths for yourself and others!

Ho ho ho, three years and Covid finally came right at the holidays 🧑🏾‍🎄🦠🕎✨
I have to say… It’s been an amazing opportunity to f*cking rest. 
Remember to keep things simple, to be kind, lessen the expectations we have for ourselves and others.
We must manage our energy, manage our expectations and stay in gratitude. Express some form of gratitude every day, and let go of control. Change is hard, but we can start to think about the holidays in a different, healthier, easier way :-)
I go both ways! Hanukkah and Christmas are my jam. To you and yours? Stay safe, keep that immune system up, mask on during the crowded crazy times, and don’t lose your sense of humor… Especially now. Happy everything everybody!
💋💋💋🕎🧑🏾‍🎄💕

Last night we bore witness to the last night of a 90 year run at the horrific Farmer John’s slaughterhouse in Vernon, CA where 10,000 pigs were slaughtered daily. This plant is closing and no more trucks will enter carrying loads of terrified 6 month piglets, but we will never forget what they endured. The stench that affects the workers, their health, and the health of anyone living there is cancer causing and unbearable. The stench never leaves and goes for miles. 
I want to thank all the incredible activists in Los Angeles @animalalliancenetwork @laanimalsave @unchained_tv who
have showed up and worked tirelessly and compassionately to make this world a better place for farm animals as well as helping so many people go plant based. 
Please make the connection. You wouldn’t send your beautiful cats and dogs to a gas chamber to kill them or eat them. All animals are created beautiful and equally! 
Under cover footage from the most brave & amazing folks at @directactioneverywhere have (Los Angeles Times and New York Times reported just today ) shown the illegal, inhumane way of “humane slaughtering“ that happens with other animals as well. It’s pure torture. Why would you want to ingest that torture into your body? People say to me, don’t show me, don’t show me, I don’t want to know. Well, you do know. And you have a choice. Make the compassionate choice, it just might save your life on the planet. 
This Smithfield Plant might have moved to another state, but we won’t stop fighting to end this war on some of the planet’s smartest beloved beings! 💕🙏🏻💕👀🐷

What a lovely getaway to the beautiful beaches of La Jolla and the stunning acres and acres of ranunculus at the Flower Fields in Carlsbad, California.
Was so important to get away and immerse myself in nature to recharge, heal the mind, body and soul. Does getting out in nature do that for you? Sometimes it’s music, my dogs, my tears, a hot bath, etc.. that grounds me, but taking care of me, makes me a better me🌸🌼💐
The pandemic has been a silver lining. It is forced me to slow down and realize what is important.
I don’t have to get it all done, cross everything off my list and say, “I gotta push through. “I gotta push through“ 
I’ve actually heard myself say, “I’ll get to it tomorrow“ 
I have to be here now. 
As my dear friend, Ivette Silberman always said, “be where your feet are” I’m sure she would approve of “be where the flowers are“ too. 
You are so worth taking care of. Your energy is precious. What could you do that is the most loving thing for yourself today? 🪻🌺💐

I went to a beautiful/purposeful event, June 11th where we commemorated a special day dedicated to our beloved canine companions—DOGS. The breathtaking Rafi Lounge Malibu, @rafilounge overlooking the majestic Pacific Ocean, served as the backdrop for this extraordinary event.

 "Yoga Stops Yulin" @yogastopsyulin Our goal was to raise awareness about the gruesome Yulin Dog Meat trade, which occurs every year on June 21st.  During Yulin, 10,000 dogs are slaughtered for human consumption. Additionally, we aimed to raise funds to support 120 dogs at The Animal Hope and Wellness Foundation @animalhopeandwellness, most of them have been saved from meat trade since 2017 and are currently living in China, awaiting either adoption or a safe place to live out their lives. Our ultimate objective is to help put an end to the annual, horrific Yulin Dog Meat Festival in China.

Every detail of this occasion meticulously honored our furry friends in the most remarkable way. We participated in a unique yoga session, exclusively designed for the YOGA STOPS YULIN campaign—a noble initiative aimed at raising awareness for the cause (for more information, please visit www.yogastopsyulin.com) 💜🙏🏼🐾
We got to interact with dog survivors from the Yulin dog meat trade. 
My amazing friend, Isabella St. James @thepugqueen had just returned from China, after dropping off seven beautiful rescues in New York, then came straight to LA with this beautiful boy! PLEASE, follow her and support her. Amazing, tireless efforts. 
We seek to elevate our vibrational energy, fostering love, compassion, and peace for all of humanity, as well as alleviating the suffering of animals and the world as a whole.

My journey with activism and a plant-based lifestyle, started with bringing awareness and helping rescue the resilient survivors of the Yulin tragedy with my badass, brilliant, activist, and filmmaker BFF @theglobalactivista 
🆘 please go to the website & donate to bring awareness and bring these beautiful, innocent creatures to the US. And… Make the connection! You would never eat your domesticated, dog or cat, so please extend that love and compassion to ALL animals💜
#YogaForYulin

I am devastated💔
I am so grateful I was allowed to watch Pee-wee when I was little, and then to work with him as an adult. 
He was hilarious, his real speaking voice was so sexy and fabulous, he would always check on me and leave me the most ridiculously inappropriate & beautiful voicemails for my birthday, he made you feel like you were the only person in the world and shared and thanked people so often and graciously.
I truly believe he allowed so many people, young, and old, to be exactly who they are, and ignite so much of our own imaginations. Our world is truly Technicolor, because of his artistry and imagination. 
I am so grateful to have met, and worked with the most amazing icons, and the additional newer cast members when we did the revival of his stage show at Club Nokia in Los Angeles.
he did a Q&A after every single show! 
He loved his fans, his friends, so deeply, always asked about my mom, my dogs and told me I could call him anytime about anything. 
Bless his heart, he would make a phone call to anybody to cheer them up and I’m borrowing his laugh right now to soothe my soul.
thank you for changing my life. Oh… I’ll never forget my audition to do all the female voices and
 understudy the ONE AND ONLY, Lynne Marie Stewart. A.k.a. Miss Yvonne. 
I was in full, crazy wardrobe, and I came twirling into the room, and he just laughed and said, “Hello Miss Yvonne’s understudy! You look beautiful today I will be reading with you“ got up, hugged me laughed told me I was beautiful and funny, and he wished me all the best in case I didn’t get cast. What a Mench. Please note in this post where he would like donations to be made. It’s important that we do that for all he did for us. 
#RIP in laughter, love and light 💔🤍💔🤍
 Your joy, sensitivity, indescribable talent, iconic presence on the WORLD will be surely missed, but never forgotten. 
forever and always, Chairy 🩵

I am embracing the power of positivity as we head back into the casting rooms! Here’s to my gray curtain in the Dining Room!! 
Positive vibes for all of us creatives for diving back in and finding the joy again in what we do :-) if you make a mistake? Use it. If you’re anxious or upset, use it. Take it from where you are, do your best and be done. 
I am forever obsessed with this human in general, but Bryan Cranston’s quotes on how his career shifted when he thought about auditioning: 
“I was going to GIVE something. I wasn’t there to GET a job. I was there to do a job. Simple as that. I was there to give a performance. If I attached to the outcome, I was setting myself up to expect, and thus to fail. My job was to focus on character. My job was to be interesting. My job was to be compelling. Take some chances. Serve the text. Enjoy the process. There was to be no predicting or manipulating, no thinking of the outcome. Outcome was irrelevant. 
I couldn’t afford any longer to approach my work as a means to an end“ 
BAM💥@bryancranston THANK YOU 
for sharing your artistry and inspiration and brilliance with us, and keeping my head screwed on straight! 

#GiveNotGet #DoYourBest #EnjoyTheProcess #TakeItFromWhereYouAre #EnjoyTheProcess #ItIsAboutTheWork #SelfTapeSuccess
